subtitleNullable: 2000 years of data for position and velocity of 11 bodies in the solar system
descriptionNullable:
The orbital solutions of the Sun, the eight planets, the dwarf planet Pluto, the Moon and the Earth-Moon Barycenter (EMB). These orbital solutions are expressed in the TDB time scale (Barycentric Dynamical Time).

The positions are the rectangular coordinates (x,y,z) in kilometers of the bodies with respect to the International Celestial Reference Frame (ICRF). The speed is in kilometers per day in the same reference frame.

The data has been generated from https://www.imcce.fr/recherche/equipes/asd/inpop/download21a
